channel.title: Getting it online?!
channel.description:
source: 317 pi okay, so i've looked at like 100 guides on how to portforward my server but like.. i've got a no-ip, I have my domain added onto it, I've typed my default gateway into my browser and done that thing or w/e, .. so now what? How do I set up my shit so other people can play? No guides explain it. I know I have to upload the client on like uppit but don't I have to change some things in the client/source? someone told me I need a seperate client for me and then one that has a different ip in it for the other people.. Idfk tbh. If someone could explain or something i'd <3 them
thanks in advance. :x
-- I have teamviewer
